external_knowledge:
- "rising tide" metaphorically refers to an increasing number of sensor readings;
- "measurements exceeding the hundred-mark" indicates sensor readings with a value greater than 100;
- "specific sensor" refers to the sensor with `sensor_id` equal to 1.

sql:
SELECT sensor_id, range_min, range_max, precision
FROM sensor_configurations
WHERE range_min > range_max;

SELECT sensors.sensor_id, sensors.sensor_name, sensor_configurations.range_min, sensor_configurations.range_max
FROM sensors
INNER JOIN sensor_configurations ON sensors.sensor_id = sensor_configurations.sensor_id;
